<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 23 at 11:15PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Buckingham
County through MIDNIGHT EDT...
At 1114 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wingina, or near Buckingham, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Buckingham...
Dillwyn...
Wingina...
New Canton...
Gold Hill...
and Centenary.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
